Purpose
This PR is to align the Ballerina compiler with class definitions and object constructor expressions introduced to the spec targetting Ballerina Swan Lake release.
With this PR object type definitions become just a type definition, which means we can't create objects with just the object type, we need to have a class or an object constructor expression to provide the implementation for an object type.
Object type def
Prev:
type Obj object {
    int i;
    function init(int i) {
        self.i = i;
    }
};
Now:
class Obj {
    int i;
    function init(int i) {
        self.i = i;
    }
}
Abstract objects
Prev:
type Obj abstract object {
    function foo(int i);
};
Now:
type Obj object {
    function foo(int i);
};
Anon objects
Prev:
function bar() {
    object { function foo() { // do something } } o = new();
}
Now:
function bar() {
    var o = object { function foo() { // do something }};
}
Fixes #25037
